1
00:00:00,530 --> 00:00:02,600
Hypnotizing him to remember

2
00:00:03,510 --> 00:00:07,820
is like forcing him towards his most fragile memories.

3
00:00:08,220 --> 00:00:10,520
The one who wants to make me forget made a mistake.

4
00:00:10,570 --> 00:00:13,170
For letting the housekeeper send me the diary.

5
00:00:13,390 --> 00:00:16,440
It’s time that you look for the culprit

6
00:00:16,870 --> 00:00:17,990
not a lover.

7
00:00:18,020 --> 00:00:19,560
Grandma will probably hypnotize me

8
00:00:19,970 --> 00:00:21,650
so that I’ll only remember things about me

9
00:00:22,150 --> 00:00:23,830
and forget about you and the murder cases.

10
00:00:24,280 --> 00:00:25,400
Then I’ll hang up.

11
00:00:25,440 --> 00:00:26,780
I have to take care of my mom.

12
00:00:27,140 --> 00:00:28,740
Pleng got hypnotized by that family.

13
00:00:28,760 --> 00:00:31,690
Your life is in your hands.

14
00:00:32,010 --> 00:00:33,210
I’ll come clean.

15
00:00:34,150 --> 00:00:35,470
Heaven must have seen

16
00:00:35,810 --> 00:00:39,150
that I’ve already repaid all the sins I did to Thunphob.

17
00:00:39,580 --> 00:00:41,310
I hate murderers like you guys.

18
00:00:41,840 --> 00:00:43,420
I hate this family.

19
00:00:55,640 --> 00:00:57,580
(My name is Botpleng Thayadon.)

20
00:00:59,260 --> 00:01:01,180
(My first love is Thunphob.)

21
00:01:03,620 --> 00:01:05,400
(My mother brought about his death.)

22
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:39,370
You still want to follow me?

23
00:01:46,900 --> 00:01:48,250
I want to go with you.

24
00:01:59,990 --> 00:02:01,760
(The only place I want to go)

25
00:02:04,340 --> 00:02:07,190
(is the place I can be free from this guilt.)

26
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:17,760
I used to think

27
00:02:19,170 --> 00:02:20,786
that there’s no truth worse than the fact that

28
00:02:20,810 --> 00:02:23,270
I might be the reason for Thunphob’s death.

29
00:02:29,270 --> 00:02:30,730
But it’s actually not true.

30
00:02:33,630 --> 00:02:36,320
The fact that someone I love killed him

31
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:39,710
is the worst.

32
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,280
If it were me.

33
00:02:49,450 --> 00:02:51,270
I would never forgive myself.

34
00:02:53,350 --> 00:02:54,600
But when it’s Mom,

35
00:02:59,770 --> 00:03:00,880
I feel guilty.

36
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:07,410
I feel like I’ve sinned.

37
00:03:13,050 --> 00:03:14,630
I shouldn’t even be here.

38
00:03:21,030 --> 00:03:22,890
I want Thunphob to forgive Mom.

39
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:27,680
I have done wrong.

40
00:03:31,320 --> 00:03:32,520
I’ve wronged him.

41
00:03:35,490 --> 00:03:36,550
I’ve wronged Mom.

42
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:44,240
And I’ve wronged you.

43
00:03:59,910 --> 00:04:04,770
There is a flower within my heart

44
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:11,440
Daisy, Daisy

45
00:04:12,010 --> 00:04:16,770
Planted one day by a glancing dart

46
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:22,430
Planted by Daisy Bell

47
00:04:30,950 --> 00:04:37,320
Whether you love me or love me not

48
00:04:40,910 --> 00:04:44,890
Sometimes it’s hard to tell

49
00:04:48,380 --> 00:04:53,430
Yet I am longing to share the lot

50
00:04:57,130 --> 00:05:01,640
A beautiful daisy bell

51
00:05:20,950 --> 00:05:22,660
You forgive me, right?

52
00:05:23,870 --> 00:05:24,870
Yeah.

53
00:07:09,270 --> 00:07:10,310
Do I look like a mess?

54
00:07:11,270 --> 00:07:12,270
Yeah.

55
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:14,650
Your eyes are dark and swollen.

56
00:07:15,010 --> 00:07:16,390
You look like a mess.

57
00:07:16,870 --> 00:07:18,870
I can’t tell if you lacked sleep

58
00:07:18,890 --> 00:07:20,330
or have been crying this whole time.

59
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:22,560
Ouch.

60
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:25,080
Ow, that hurts.

61
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:30,680
Is this a time to joke around?

62
00:07:32,030 --> 00:07:33,170
I mean

63
00:07:34,650 --> 00:07:36,120
things have escalated this far

64
00:07:38,310 --> 00:07:39,780
but I still make you comfort me.

65
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:44,600
I’ve been talking big about accepting the truth.

66
00:07:50,870 --> 00:07:52,230
Even though you are hurt

67
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,390
no less than I am.

68
00:07:57,970 --> 00:07:59,420
Or even more.

69
00:08:00,270 --> 00:08:01,860
No matter what happens,

70
00:08:03,250 --> 00:08:05,140
it can never change

71
00:08:06,310 --> 00:08:07,560
the fact that I love you.

72
00:08:18,890 --> 00:08:20,660
Then it can’t change

73
00:08:23,080 --> 00:08:24,780
the fact that I love you a lot, too.

74
00:08:32,540 --> 00:08:33,600
And are your eyes

75
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:36,510
the result of lack of sleep

76
00:08:38,550 --> 00:08:39,680
or did you just cry?

77
00:08:41,510 --> 00:08:42,760
If I say it’s the latter,

78
00:08:43,630 --> 00:08:44,760
it wouldn’t sound cool.

79
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,520
You can let me be cool for once.

80
00:08:47,990 --> 00:08:49,830
I want to be the one to comfort you sometimes.

81
00:08:49,950 --> 00:08:51,670
Here I am for you to comfort me.

82
00:08:59,990 --> 00:09:01,990
Please don’t cry alone again, Pleng.

83
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:09,110
There’s only your heart

84
00:09:11,030 --> 00:09:12,810
that can make me feel safe.

85
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:36,400
And…

86
00:09:39,850 --> 00:09:41,160
About my mom,

87
00:09:42,540 --> 00:09:43,840
what are you going to do next?

88
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:49,560
No moves taken since yesterday.

89
00:09:50,570 --> 00:09:53,300
Not even an attempt to search for you.

90
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:55,480
Why?

91
00:09:56,490 --> 00:09:57,590
I don’t get it.

92
00:09:58,300 --> 00:10:00,230
There are 3 reasons.

93
00:10:02,390 --> 00:10:03,860
They might be sure

94
00:10:05,290 --> 00:10:07,010
that no one can press charges against them.

95
00:10:09,350 --> 00:10:11,030
Or they might trust

96
00:10:13,130 --> 00:10:14,700
that you won’t hurt them.

97
00:10:19,670 --> 00:10:20,850
What about the other one?

98
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,530
They don’t try to run

99
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,600
because there’s nowhere for them to run.

100
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:46,280
The reason why I dared enter your house

101
00:10:47,370 --> 00:10:49,410
was because I’ve been investigating it for a while.

102
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:52,280
There was no security.

103
00:10:52,890 --> 00:10:54,330
Only day maids.

104
00:10:55,730 --> 00:10:57,746
As for those who used to be
your grandpa’s underlings,

105
00:10:57,770 --> 00:10:59,410
they only have respect for him now.

106
00:11:00,330 --> 00:11:01,680
There’s no influence left

107
00:11:02,250 --> 00:11:03,450
at the police station.

108
00:11:09,450 --> 00:11:11,930
Grandma has never talked to me
about my family’s money, either.

109
00:11:13,510 --> 00:11:15,560
I’ve been using my own money.

110
00:11:18,670 --> 00:11:19,670
Right now,

111
00:11:20,990 --> 00:11:22,660
if your family were to run away,

112
00:11:23,550 --> 00:11:24,550
it would be hard to do.

113
00:11:25,950 --> 00:11:27,080
Do you mean that.

114
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:32,120
I’m the key to my family’s death or survival?

115
00:11:37,530 --> 00:11:38,640
You’re the only one

116
00:11:39,590 --> 00:11:41,300
who can solve this.

117
00:11:52,090 --> 00:11:55,480
Should I pretend I don’t know anything

118
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:57,850
then you can arrest my mother.

119
00:11:57,880 --> 00:11:58,880
Would that be easier?

120
00:12:06,030 --> 00:12:07,170
You wanted Thunphob

121
00:12:08,490 --> 00:12:10,030
to forgive your mother, didn’t you?

122
00:12:20,300 --> 00:12:21,596
Is this why you weren’t in a hurry

123
00:12:21,620 --> 00:12:23,120
to get me back to Bangkok?

124
00:12:27,670 --> 00:12:29,270
Someone once told me

125
00:12:31,420 --> 00:12:32,660
that you should pick vegetables

126
00:12:33,190 --> 00:12:34,340
in the evening.

127
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:41,970
I read something that said

128
00:12:42,450 --> 00:12:43,490
you should pick vegetables

129
00:12:44,890 --> 00:12:46,400
when you want to eat it.

130
00:12:49,470 --> 00:12:51,100
Don’t you want to eat some today?

131
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:53,980
I’ve already packed your clothes.

132
00:12:55,990 --> 00:12:57,710
Just in case you want to stay a night here.

133
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:05,700
Then…

134
00:13:07,450 --> 00:13:09,450
Can you please take me home tomorrow?

135
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:26,080
Were you stealing a look at me?

136
00:13:27,490 --> 00:13:28,490
No.

137
00:13:32,390 --> 00:13:33,710
Are you secretly in love with me?

138
00:13:36,680 --> 00:13:37,760
Hasn’t it been a while now?

139
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:43,400
What’s on your mind?

140
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:46,570
Can you read my mind?

141
00:13:47,870 --> 00:13:48,970
I want to ask.

142
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:51,820
I’m thinking that

143
00:13:53,140 --> 00:13:54,850
it’s so nice to have you.

144
00:13:56,550 --> 00:13:58,340
I think you have such a big heart

145
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:00,130
and so warm.

146
00:14:01,430 --> 00:14:02,890
I also think that

147
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:05,320
with you.

148
00:14:07,010 --> 00:14:08,780
I can get through anything.

149
00:14:12,780 --> 00:14:13,780
What about you?

150
00:14:14,060 --> 00:14:15,060
What are you thinking?

151
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:18,490
Why are you still here with me now?

152
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:28,760
I’ve never thought I would sit by a river with anyone

153
00:14:29,980 --> 00:14:31,440
until you came along.

154
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:50,920
A daisy?

155
00:14:54,790 --> 00:14:57,210
I know there are times
when you want to be alone.

156
00:14:58,090 --> 00:14:59,770
When you want to spend time with yourself.

157
00:15:00,290 --> 00:15:01,290
And I

158
00:15:02,030 --> 00:15:03,430
won’t disturb you.

159
00:15:04,940 --> 00:15:06,760
But I don’t want you to think that

160
00:15:07,220 --> 00:15:08,490
you have no one.

161
00:15:09,420 --> 00:15:11,070
I want you to know that

162
00:15:11,110 --> 00:15:13,460
you’ll always find me right here.

163
00:15:28,470 --> 00:15:32,230
You can’t stop my heart

164
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:34,080
from following you.

165
00:15:56,830 --> 00:15:58,370
I can read your mind, too.

166
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:01,650
I think saying our heart aligns

167
00:16:02,110 --> 00:16:03,580
would sound more romantic.

168
00:16:05,450 --> 00:16:06,450
Okay.

169
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:08,140
Our hearts align.

170
00:16:17,240 --> 00:16:18,240
You know what?

171
00:16:20,230 --> 00:16:23,050
You’re not the second violin in Canon in D.

172
00:16:28,170 --> 00:16:29,970
But you’re the first note

173
00:16:31,030 --> 00:16:32,650
in my Daisy Bell.

174
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:34,440
Thank you.

175
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:48,240
Yes?

176
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:04,490
Are you sure

177
00:17:04,790 --> 00:17:06,180
about going home alone?

178
00:17:07,410 --> 00:17:08,410
Yes.

179
00:17:08,840 --> 00:17:10,490
Let me talk to her myself.

180
00:17:11,360 --> 00:17:13,500
It might be easier when there’s just me.

181
00:17:14,040 --> 00:17:16,150
Tanu confessed that he killed everyone.

182
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:18,200
Don’t you think it’s better

183
00:17:18,650 --> 00:17:20,680
to let everything end like this?

184
00:17:24,040 --> 00:17:25,860
If I knew my mom did something wrong

185
00:17:25,880 --> 00:17:26,990
and just let it slide,

186
00:17:28,190 --> 00:17:30,390
I wouldn’t dare ask for Thunphob’s forgiveness.

187
00:17:31,540 --> 00:17:32,950
And I wouldn’t dare love you.

188
00:17:42,850 --> 00:17:43,850
I love you.

189
00:17:44,390 --> 00:17:45,390
I know.

190
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:46,780
I knew it even before you did.

191
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:52,340
I’m not walking in there alone.

192
00:17:53,710 --> 00:17:54,860
I have this with me.

193
00:18:42,040 --> 00:18:43,040
Yes?

194
00:18:46,090 --> 00:18:47,650
Can you come to BID right now?

195
00:19:00,130 --> 00:19:01,340
You’re back?

196
00:19:15,600 --> 00:19:16,650
Professor.

197
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:19,840
I’ve already sent you the file

198
00:19:19,890 --> 00:19:21,320
with Tanu’s full confession.

199
00:19:21,620 --> 00:19:23,910
This is the behavior observation form.

200
00:19:23,930 --> 00:19:24,930
Thank you.

201
00:19:26,990 --> 00:19:30,050
Tanu has already admitted to all his crimes

202
00:19:30,550 --> 00:19:34,070
why do both you and Inspector Dao

203
00:19:34,090 --> 00:19:35,770
make it seem like there’s something wrong?

204
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:36,900
Dao too?

205
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:38,040
Yes.

206
00:19:38,330 --> 00:19:40,780
After Tanu came clean,

207
00:19:41,050 --> 00:19:43,270
Inspector Dao has been re-watching

208
00:19:43,300 --> 00:19:44,370
the confession video.

209
00:19:44,820 --> 00:19:46,620
She seemed stressed out for a while.

210
00:19:46,650 --> 00:19:47,660
Then she just left.

211
00:19:49,390 --> 00:19:52,269
Lt. Nim, let me see that interrogation video.

212
00:19:52,320 --> 00:19:54,160
I’ll consult with my investigation team first.

213
00:19:54,380 --> 00:19:55,389
Sure, professor.

214
00:19:58,400 --> 00:19:59,941
Hey, this is urgent.

215
00:20:09,350 --> 00:20:10,763
Tanu’s already confessed

216
00:20:11,940 --> 00:20:13,500
that he was the one who killed Thunphob

217
00:20:14,603 --> 00:20:16,600
and the other 2
who were involved with our family.

218
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:22,509
Can you tell me.

219
00:20:24,510 --> 00:20:26,669
When you say you brought about Thunphob’s death,

220
00:20:27,490 --> 00:20:28,670
what did you mean by that?

221
00:20:32,580 --> 00:20:34,014
You must want to hear that

222
00:20:34,065 --> 00:20:37,003
we’re the ones who killed him, huh?

223
00:20:42,520 --> 00:20:44,327
I just want the truth.

224
00:20:45,110 --> 00:20:46,647
I want to know why you and Mom

225
00:20:46,683 --> 00:20:48,283
keep hypnotising me to make me forget.

226
00:20:50,350 --> 00:20:52,101
Or is there any of my memory

227
00:20:53,340 --> 00:20:55,185
that has to do with everyone’s death?

228
00:20:57,890 --> 00:20:59,149
Including Dad’s, right?

229
00:20:59,301 --> 00:21:00,080
Nonsense.

230
00:21:00,109 --> 00:21:01,109
Mom!

231
00:21:10,120 --> 00:21:11,141
Botpleng.

232
00:21:12,189 --> 00:21:13,309
The thing is…

233
00:21:17,370 --> 00:21:18,967
Oh, Dao.

234
00:21:20,010 --> 00:21:21,083
Inspector Dao.

235
00:21:25,600 --> 00:21:27,265
Aren’t you supposed to be with Tankhun?

236
00:21:32,007 --> 00:21:33,425
The Governor sent me the verdict

237
00:21:33,454 --> 00:21:35,774
saying that those involved in the concession
were innocent.

238
00:21:36,130 --> 00:21:38,000
The rumor spread from the slander

239
00:21:38,029 --> 00:21:39,629
stemming from a local politics conflict.

240
00:21:39,850 --> 00:21:42,523
Doctor Chomphon was the one
who saw things through

241
00:21:42,560 --> 00:21:44,050
after Pleng’s dad died.

242
00:21:45,590 --> 00:21:47,694
Botpleng’s dad died due to a heart attack.

243
00:21:47,716 --> 00:21:49,010
He was not murdered.

244
00:21:49,960 --> 00:21:51,229
That’s not possible.

245
00:21:52,276 --> 00:21:54,280
If that case was done right,

246
00:21:54,341 --> 00:21:55,229
then why did someone try

247
00:21:55,287 --> 00:21:57,563
to make Inspector Dao stop investigating?

248
00:22:00,250 --> 00:22:01,890
Inspector Dao investigated this case too?

249
00:22:02,050 --> 00:22:03,050
Yes.

250
00:22:03,170 --> 00:22:05,730
It was her first case after moving here.

251
00:22:06,130 --> 00:22:07,170
What’s going on?

252
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:09,847
Why did Inspector Dao have to deal with this case?

253
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:14,363
It was Doctor Chomphon
who cleared the case for Botpleng’s dad.

254
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:16,465
He’s also Inspector Dao’s father.

255
00:22:17,460 --> 00:22:18,460
It was Dao?

256
00:22:18,970 --> 00:22:20,530
Guys, excuse me.

257
00:22:21,381 --> 00:22:22,381
Tankhun!

258
00:22:24,410 --> 00:22:25,912
(Urgent report!)

259
00:22:25,941 --> 00:22:29,570
(Tanu, the suspect of the serial murder case)

260
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:30,814
(has managed to escape.)

261
00:22:31,290 --> 00:22:32,370
How did you do that?

262
00:22:33,310 --> 00:22:34,310
Which one?

263
00:22:36,494 --> 00:22:37,934
If it’s Tanu’s case,

264
00:22:38,630 --> 00:22:39,630
that wasn’t hard.

265
00:22:40,280 --> 00:22:41,985
I have my people.

266
00:22:43,560 --> 00:22:45,207
Or is it about your mom and grandma?

267
00:22:47,190 --> 00:22:48,610
That’s even easier.

268
00:22:49,930 --> 00:22:51,156
Those at your house,

269
00:22:51,185 --> 00:22:52,778
they’re all my people.

270
00:22:54,780 --> 00:22:56,676
I just tell them to spike the drinks

271
00:22:56,712 --> 00:22:57,949
before I get there.

272
00:22:59,010 --> 00:23:00,647
But it went wrong because

273
00:23:01,060 --> 00:23:02,152
you happened to be there

274
00:23:02,189 --> 00:23:03,510
instead of with Tankhun.

275
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:06,734
So you’ll have to

276
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:09,774
become another one of Tanu’s victims.

277
00:23:11,430 --> 00:23:12,603
You let Tanu go

278
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:14,349
to put the blame on him?

279
00:23:15,510 --> 00:23:17,294
It’s too late to be smart now.

280
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:20,960
We’re almost there.

281
00:23:21,820 --> 00:23:22,880
Get ready.

282
00:23:30,680 --> 00:23:32,429
(Your life is in your hands.)

283
00:23:32,465 --> 00:23:34,065
(Pick a smarter choice)

284
00:23:34,116 --> 00:23:37,840
(and let the Thayadon face their karma.)

285
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:39,934
Damn it!

286
00:23:39,949 --> 00:23:41,381
Why did I just check it out?

287
00:23:41,770 --> 00:23:43,330
What’s up with the interrogation video?

288
00:23:43,860 --> 00:23:45,570
It wasn’t just an interrogation video.

289
00:23:45,830 --> 00:23:47,585
Dao intentionally framed Tanu

290
00:23:48,220 --> 00:23:49,621
and Botpleng’s family.

291
00:23:49,930 --> 00:23:51,112
Dao is behind all this.

292
00:23:51,390 --> 00:23:53,229
Dao is the daughter of Dr. Chomphon

293
00:23:53,265 --> 00:23:54,821
who was close to Botpleng’s family.

294
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:56,763
That means…

295
00:23:57,400 --> 00:24:00,640
The reason why she dug up the concession case

296
00:24:00,669 --> 00:24:02,007
was to hurt Madame.

297
00:24:02,540 --> 00:24:03,898
What’s even going on?

298
00:24:03,956 --> 00:24:04,956
I don’t know.

299
00:24:05,230 --> 00:24:06,640
I only know that right now,

300
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:08,661
Pleng is in trouble.

301
00:24:08,705 --> 00:24:10,029
Damn it, Pleng.

302
00:24:10,058 --> 00:24:11,156
Why did you go with them?

303
00:24:12,010 --> 00:24:13,869
I have him carry a GPS device with him.

304
00:24:17,870 --> 00:24:19,578
Keep this with you at all times.

305
00:24:19,614 --> 00:24:20,814
You can keep it in your socks

306
00:24:20,858 --> 00:24:21,883
so you wouldn’t lose it.

307
00:24:21,927 --> 00:24:24,821
It’s accurate and harder to kill the signal

308
00:24:24,858 --> 00:24:26,218
compared to the ones on the phone.

309
00:24:26,300 --> 00:24:27,920
You should keep one too

310
00:24:27,970 --> 00:24:29,389
so that I can find you as well.

311
00:24:32,570 --> 00:24:33,738
You don’t know

312
00:24:33,781 --> 00:24:35,549
that I started buying things in pairs

313
00:24:36,190 --> 00:24:37,680
since the first time I met you.

314
00:24:39,745 --> 00:24:40,698
Okay.

315
00:24:40,734 --> 00:24:41,734
I get it.

316
00:25:02,140 --> 00:25:03,541
Can you go faster?

317
00:25:11,880 --> 00:25:12,880
Mom.

318
00:25:13,750 --> 00:25:14,887
How are you doing?

319
00:25:15,320 --> 00:25:16,356
Are you hurt anywhere?

320
00:25:17,290 --> 00:25:18,290
Kan.

321
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:18,952
Kan.

322
00:25:18,974 --> 00:25:19,974
Mom.

323
00:25:49,420 --> 00:25:50,654
Why did you do this?

324
00:25:51,280 --> 00:25:53,403
I’ve been taking good care of you all this time.

325
00:25:55,440 --> 00:25:57,360
Taking good care of me?

326
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:00,680
Bullshit.

327
00:26:02,020 --> 00:26:03,020
You

328
00:26:03,370 --> 00:26:05,600
were the one who ruined my family.

329
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:14,000
Doctor!

330
00:26:14,650 --> 00:26:16,778
(Almost every day at dawn, )

331
00:26:16,829 --> 00:26:18,334
(Dad would visit your house.)

332
00:26:18,900 --> 00:26:20,072
See that?

333
00:26:20,450 --> 00:26:22,450
Your dad is a traitor!

334
00:26:22,830 --> 00:26:25,170
See what your dad does?

335
00:26:38,250 --> 00:26:39,250
Mom!

336
00:26:40,152 --> 00:26:41,152
Mom!

337
00:26:41,580 --> 00:26:42,545
Mom!

338
00:26:42,574 --> 00:26:43,701
Mom!

339
00:26:43,730 --> 00:26:45,520
Wake up, Mom!

340
00:26:45,556 --> 00:26:47,214
Mom!

341
00:26:47,250 --> 00:26:48,421
Mom!

342
00:26:53,420 --> 00:26:54,420
Dad.

343
00:26:56,487 --> 00:26:58,490
You’re still choosing her even now?

344
00:26:59,640 --> 00:27:00,618
It was because you and she

345
00:27:00,661 --> 00:27:02,029
that Mom died.

346
00:27:07,970 --> 00:27:08,970
Nonsense.

347
00:27:10,380 --> 00:27:11,614
There’s nothing going on.

348
00:27:12,520 --> 00:27:13,570
I’m a doctor.

349
00:27:14,510 --> 00:27:15,840
I’m just there to treat her.

350
00:27:16,680 --> 00:27:18,480
You and your mom are crazy.

351
00:27:40,480 --> 00:27:42,210
The reason why Dr. Chomphon was dead

352
00:27:42,792 --> 00:27:44,790
can’t have been an accident.

353
00:27:48,690 --> 00:27:49,716
That’s right.

354
00:27:51,240 --> 00:27:53,970
You guys ruined my family.

355
00:27:54,807 --> 00:27:56,810
You turned me into an orphan.

356
00:27:57,309 --> 00:27:59,310
Do you think everything you did

357
00:27:59,345 --> 00:28:01,061
can make up for that?

358
00:28:03,810 --> 00:28:05,672
What about that housekeeper and the clerk?

359
00:28:05,694 --> 00:28:07,056
What did they have to do with this?

360
00:28:07,080 --> 00:28:08,232
Why did you kill them?

361
00:28:08,261 --> 00:28:09,280
Why do you want to know?

362
00:28:10,625 --> 00:28:12,630
You’d soon be dead just like them.

363
00:28:13,190 --> 00:28:14,960
So that I can tell the dead

364
00:28:15,520 --> 00:28:16,996
how evil you are.

365
00:28:18,916 --> 00:28:20,458
F*ck!

366
00:28:20,509 --> 00:28:21,803
How can you guys not realize it?!

367
00:28:21,825 --> 00:28:23,650
You guys are the wicked ones!

368
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:25,774
You also killed Thunphob.

369
00:28:28,230 --> 00:28:29,767
I found the diary

370
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:31,534
so I knew

371
00:28:32,120 --> 00:28:34,429
that Thunphob died
because he came to see you.

372
00:28:36,030 --> 00:28:37,030
So right now,

373
00:28:37,980 --> 00:28:40,232
I’ll have to take revenge on everyone’s behalf.

374
00:28:41,060 --> 00:28:42,060
That day,

375
00:28:42,470 --> 00:28:45,374
I had the housekeeper kid send you the diary.

376
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:50,858
(That kid)

377
00:28:50,910 --> 00:28:53,905
(was the son of the one
who helped you cheat on the concession.)

378
00:28:53,941 --> 00:28:55,490
(So he has to pay.)

379
00:28:58,530 --> 00:29:00,872
Hello? I’m already here.

380
00:29:00,909 --> 00:29:02,370
Are you coming?

381
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:03,665
(That lady was the clerk)

382
00:29:03,709 --> 00:29:05,709
(who helped your dad cheat.)

383
00:29:05,752 --> 00:29:07,040
(All I had to do)

384
00:29:07,083 --> 00:29:09,556
(was to place the fishing line at your house.)

385
00:29:10,650 --> 00:29:12,145
So you sent the diary to me

386
00:29:12,181 --> 00:29:13,810
